1.title: Jessica & Justin
1.plot: Deatsville, Alabama's Jessica and Justin already have a baby, so now they've decided to tie the knot...in a mud pit! Justin plans to go all out by taking his buddies along to help him pick out a wedding dress.

2.title: Tina & Chase
2.plot: Tina and Chase plan to top their wedding cake with stuffed squirrels dressed as bride and groom. Chase loves his pistol packin' bride-to-be almost as much as he loves his taxidermy art.

3.title: Jessica & Kevin
3.plot: In Kempner, Texas, nurse-with-a-wild-side Jessica is about to become the fourth wife of rock crawling addict Kevin. In keeping with their love of rugged terrain, the two are getting hitched atop a rock pile.

4.title: Jennifer & Chris
4.plot: Jennifer and Chris are Italian and Cuban Rednecks from the Redneck melting pot of Punta Gorda, Florida who want to get married at the same mud pit where Chris first laid eyes on her.

5.title: Alicia & Brad
5.plot: Brad, of Corsicana, Texas, and fiancÃ©e Alicia are planning on having a redneck carnival for their wedding - complete with an archery competition, fool-proof horseshoes and a dunk tank filled with beer.

6.title: Kim & Mike
6.plot: In Spiro, Oklahoma, Kim and Mike are about to marry each other - for the second time. To make sure this wedding's different from their first one, they're bringing in everything from a fishing boat to a cake made out of giant blocks of cheese.

7.title: Baby: Ashley and Lee
7.plot: The small town of Bithlo, Florida is about to get a little bigger with the arrival of Ashley and Lee's baby. The proud parents-to-be are going to do everything to insure that their first child is 100% pure redneck.

8.title: Intervention: Bonnie Johnson and Batten Family
8.plot: Bonnie Johnson was a little redneck growing up in a single-wide trailer in Tennessee and now she's all grown up living the good life. But her still-countrified family want to get her back in touch with her muddin', huntin' and 4 wheeling' roots.

9.title: Sara and Joe
9.plot: Joe is a welder who first started chasing Sara in the eighth grade. These two camo-loving lovebirds from Fredericktown, Missouri are about to get hitched in a wild wedding including everything from horse manure skeeball to bubble-wrap sumo wrestling.

10.title: Lindsay and Russell
10.plot: In Darien, Georgia, Lindsay is about to marry best friend and hunting partner, Russell. To make sure everyone has a great time, they're painting bowling balls to look like pool balls for a giant game of lawn billiards.

1.title: Anna and Carl
1.plot: Anna and Carl are like two crazy kids in love. Carl is a proud redneck through and through who spends his days growing pumpkins, tending to horses, and sharing fresh chicken eggs with his family and friends

2.title: Suzy and Ron
2.plot: Ron and Suzy live in the horse town of Norco, California.

3.title: Geneva and Kyle
3.plot: Geneva and Kyle are 18 years-old, redneck, and in love. Deep in the Appalachian Mountains of Tennessee, this worry-free couple chose the public golf course with its busy driving range for their chapel." Fearing neither flying golf balls nor Geneva's "traditional" parents, they're goin' whole hog with all the fixins - pork rinds, ground souse meat, and pickled pig's feet. Attire is camo for all the guests. A tractor brings in the bride. That is, if the groom survives his own bachelor party - a full on bottle rocket war, where the fireworks are aimed at each other! ...

4.title: Christy and Kevin
4.plot: Christy is a vet tech that's never met a stray animal that she didn't bring home.

5.title: Gail and John
5.plot: John and Gail, two newspaper delivery carriers, are planning a redneck bash on the eastern shores of Maryland.

6.title: Tami and Brad
6.plot: In Puyallup, Washington, Tami and Brad are getting hitched the Northwest Redneck style, with rain, mud, guns, quads and plenty of beer guzzling fun.

7.title: Amber and John
7.plot: Amber, 21, and John, 25, live in Statenville, Georgia, a town so small it has only one stoplight. John's a mud bogging, hog hunting, proud good ol' boy. Amber is right there with him, ready to skin the hog or any other animal that John happens to catch.

8.title: Kelli and Ron
8.plot: Kelly andÂ Ron are both from small towns in Western Pennsylvania.

1.title: Anna & Bo
1.plot: The first episode of the second season of MY BIG REDNECK WEDDING features Anna and Bo of Verbena, Ala., a couple whose non-traditional wedding includes the fact that they are brother and sister

2.title: Jeanne and Phil
2.plot: Episode two features Phil, a tractor loving nudist from Maryland found who he calls his "BBW", Jeanne, over the internet.

3.title: Emily and Eric
3.plot: Episode three features Emily, a former punk rocker who turned redneck for the guy of her dreams, Eric, whose favorite pastime is collecting raccoon privates.

4.title: Amyie and George
4.plot: The 11-year age difference doesn't affect Amyie's love for her sweetheart of three months, George. The wedding/family reunion included a slip and slide, Jell-O wresting, a hot dog eating contest, and go cart racing.

5.title: Sabrena and Blair
5.plot: After five failed marriages between the two of them, Sabrena and Blair are ready to tie the knot for good.

6.title: Rawni and Rob
6.plot: Rawni and Rob have known each other since elementary school and started dating in high school. Being two young, crazy kids, they didn't know they were meant to be together.

7.title: Lynn and Graeme
7.plot: In Lake Wales, FL, the groom literally flips a car after he and his bride are walked down the aisle by their pets.

8.title: Shawna and Vince
8.plot: Sprague, Wash., gives us this loving duo (Shawna and Vince) who are getting married as an excuse for a good party and a way to blend their families of five kids.

1.title: Sandy and David
1.plot: She's loved him since he was the neighborhood paperboy. Now it's finally time for Sandra and David to get hitched and their doing it duck-hunting style.

2.title: Melissa and Bradley
2.plot: Melissa and Bradley are from Venedocia, Ohio. This couple brings together a mess of kids and a whole lot of fun.

3.title: Kimberly and Heinz
3.plot: Kimberly and Heinz are from Portersville, Penn. These high school sweethearts were originally supposed to get married 10 years ago but are only now making it to the truck bed/altar. The wedding is at the Git-R-Done Chapel in the middle of Ohio's famed Yankee Lake mud bog.

4.title: Amy and Keith
4.plot: Amy and Keith are from Wyoming, Mich. One dumpster truck driving bride plus one semi-driving groom equals one totally truck themed wedding. The vows are filled with on-the-road sentiments, and the traditional wedding attire is topped off with accessories like hard hats, truck boots and a cane made from a gearshift stick.

5.title: Jamie and Jimmy
5.plot: The wedding is just one of the biggest redneck things happening for this couple, Jamie and Jimmie's first home, a double wide, is delivered just in time for the big event. To commemorate this, they attempt to make a doublewide shaped cake.

6.title: Vickie and Brandon
6.plot: Before he met Vickie, Brandon's last serious relationship was with a cow. But despite a 13-year age difference, Vickie and Brandon will unite in marriage. On the way to the altar, pigs will be castrated and frogs will be skewered - all in the name of "appetizers."

7.title: Terri and Greg
7.plot: It's a double wedding when Terri and Greg and their dogs Hemmy and Droopy exchange vows. Terri's a tomboy with pink hair and a purple dress and he's a good-ole-boy who's a little gun shy about heading to the altar. But he buys he beloved a rifle for a wedding present anyway, as she plows ahead with plans, making a moon pie cake shaped like a fish, buying a wedding night wardrobe and attaching a spittoon to her bouquet.

8.title: Leann and Gary
8.plot: Gary is a karaoke singing, racecar driving, all-American guy who met his gal when he went to get a sandwich at the deli where she was working. Now he will triumphantly take her as his bride in Victory Lane at his favorite racetrack. Though not her dream wedding, Leann is getting into the spirit, learning a song to sing for Gary and getting into a go-cart crash while Gary busy himself making a ring out of car parts and trying to find the right accessories for his racing suit tux. It truly is a mad dash to the altar for these two.

9.title: Tamzen and Kevin
9.plot: This 300 pound bride and her 105 pound groom love each other as much as they love to fight, which is a lot. It's a rocky path to the altar as Kevin tries to hunt squirrels for wedding food and a diamond for Tamzen's ring. A visit to the county clerk to get their marriage license and getting the chicken house location ready for the ceremony with no help from Kevin is Tamzen's big focus. After a touching and humorous ceremony, the newlyweds take to a boxing ring to settle their differences once and for all.

10.title: LeeAnne and Nathan
10.plot: These two horse lovers met at a stable. And they bring that love into their country themed wedding with "horse turd roses" as decoration and even a game with horse poop filled water balloons at the reception. Other than the poop, there's the matter of LeeAnne finding a suitably tacky dress, a 'coon hunt bachelor party and the armadillo cake. It's different and it's hilarious!

11.title: Kathy and Gator
11.plot: For 14 years these two have been in love and playing house with her six kids. Now they are making it official at a mud bog. This episode shows how family and friends join together to make this occasion a day to remember for these two. They've got a cake replica of the bog, a hubcap covered golf cart, and some interesting outfits for Gator and his groomsmen. And mud. Lots and lots of mud.

12.title: Jessica and Jon
12.plot: After meeting on the internet, this young couple doesn't have much in the way of plans for their wedding, but they're having one, regardless. We follow their journey as they find a location, a dress and figure out how to pay for everything, like auctioning off their bridesmaids and groomsmen! They pull it off in a way that you'll have to see to believe!

13.title: Christy and Chris
13.plot: It took two years of her looking his way to catch his eye, but now that she has Christy and Chris are headed straight to the altar in this muddy extravaganza. They've come up with a lot of unique elements, like an ice-chest shaped groom's cake, a beer can opener/garter, and some freshly painted hunting arrows Christy's gift. If you like dancing and mattress surfing, you're going to love this wedding!

14.title: Carol and Carlis
14.plot: This fiery redhead bride and her former high school sweetheart found true love the second time around and are having a very unconventional wedding to cement their relationship. They've got seven kids between them taking part in the ceremony; a possum that Chris is hoping will be food for the reception, and boxers and wife beaters for wedding outfits. This one is chock full of good old-fashioned family fun, including the ever popular belching contest and a large scale food fight. You'll be talking about it for years.

15.title: Taran and James
15.plot: For once the groom really wants to participate in the wedding planning, but his bride doesn't appreciate his ideas at all - mostly because his ideas include trying to catch jumping fish in garbage bags, spray-painting her wedding dress and a raccoon hide covered archway. But they do make it down the aisle where their friend/occasional stripper/wannabe comedian unties them for life. And then they celebrate with a ride on a recliner through the mud. It's truly must see CMT.

16.title: Cindy and Gene
16.plot: It's the third time around for these two, and Junior is letting Cindy take care of all the details. Sure he shows up for his fireworks filled bachelor party and the wedding, but she's out clam digging, customizing a sexy red dress, and practicing their prom queen wave. The ceremony itself is a real tearjerker, especially for the minister and the love is infectious. A good time is sure to be had by all who tune in.

-1.title: The 12 Days of Redneck Christmas
-1.plot: After documenting redneck couples' outrageous journeys down the aisle, host Tom Arnold finds families with equally as unique holiday traditions in the special, THE 12 DAYS OF REDNECK CHRISTMAS.

imdb.title: My Big Redneck Wedding
plot: A reality TV program that documents down-home country couples as they prepare to take a trip down the aisles of matrimony.::Anonymous
